// token passed in. So `f(c: Cap)` with `Cap` ambient is a VALID annotation —
// possession via parameter is allowed, NO E2212. The program compiles and runs
// (`f` is never called; `main` returns 0; the ambient capability param drops as
// a ZST no-op). Poison: if the possession check bans `ambient` too (not just
// `deny`), this fixture errors out → goes red = proof the check is not too wide.
capability Cap ambient

function f(c: Cap) -> Integer { return 0 }

